  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou2-hemolysis-absolute",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/monte-carlo-uq-samples-cou2"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-bench-cou2-a",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis validation — FDA pump at VAD operating points",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations. Predicted NIH values exceeded measured values by 18–42 % across all test points. Validation metric (E_val) exceeds the acceptance threshold defined at MRL 5. A 2000-sample Monte Carlo UQ campaign was executed to propagate inlet boundary-condition and viscosity uncertainties; the resulting 95 % prediction interval brackets all experimental points, but the interval width (±31 %) is judged too large to support absolute hemolysis acceptance for a Class III device. Sensitivity indices were computed internally within the UQ campaign and are discussed in the UQ report; structured linkage to a formal sensitivity-analysis record is deferred pending harmonisation of the sensitivity-analysis taxonomy with the V&V 40 credibility framework."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-bench-cou2-b",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Grid-convergence and temporal-discretisation validation — VAD impeller passage",
      "description": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation performed on impeller-passage mesh sizes of 1.2 M, 4.8 M, and 19.2 M cells. Grid-convergence index (GCI) on NIH is 9.7 % on the fine grid, exceeding the MRL 5 target of ≤3 %. Temporal discretisation study with three time-step sizes confirms second-order convergence in velocity but first-order convergence in shear-stress derived hemolysis scalar, contributing to elevated discretisation uncertainty."
    }
  ],
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4037671",
  "wasAttributedTo": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/fda-cdrh-computational-modeling",
